<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17040&amp;p=213593#p213593"><![CDATA[
Technically, the background layer allows for 3 colours + transparency. The first entry in any subpalette is really that transparency, but its value acts as a flood-fill for the screen colour behind that background layer. <br /><br />If a sprite is drawn behind the background layer, you will notice that slot 0 in the subpalette does not cover that sprite.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7508">FrankenGraphics</a> — Wed Feb 14, 2018 10:13 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
